From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: wifi: ath11k: do not warn about HTT event 48

The NSS offload firmware periodically sends HTT T2H message type 48
(0x30) on every radio start; the driver has no consumer for it and
logged "htt event 48 not handled" at warning level on each occurrence.
Give the type a name and drop it quietly.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_rx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_rx.c
@@ -2173,6 +2173,11 @@ void ath11k_dp_htt_htc_t2h_msg_handler(s
 	case HTT_T2H_MSG_TYPE_BKPRESSURE_EVENT_IND:
 		ath11k_htt_backpressure_event_handler(ab, skb);
 		break;
+	case HTT_T2H_MSG_TYPE_NSS_PERIODIC_STATS:
+		/* Periodic indication from the NSS offload firmware; this
+		 * driver has nothing to feed it into, drop it quietly.
+		 */
+		break;
 	default:
 		ath11k_warn(ab, "htt event %d not handled\n", type);
 		break;
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp.h
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp.h
@@ -1099,6 +1099,7 @@ enum htt_t2h_msg_type {
 	HTT_T2H_MSG_TYPE_PPDU_STATS_IND = 0x1d,
 	HTT_T2H_MSG_TYPE_EXT_STATS_CONF = 0x1c,
 	HTT_T2H_MSG_TYPE_BKPRESSURE_EVENT_IND = 0x24,
+	HTT_T2H_MSG_TYPE_NSS_PERIODIC_STATS = 0x30,
 };
 
 #define HTT_TARGET_VERSION_MAJOR 3
